The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Tight security for Asian meet 

New Delhi: Despite concerns about players security in the light of the deadly serial blasts in the city on October 29, the 14th Asian Archery Championship will commences from November 5, Archery Association of India (AAI) president Vijay Kumar Malhotra told here on Thursday. 

Competitors from 20 countries will be participating in the meet. Several countries as well as the Asian Archery Federation (AAF) had expressed concern over the security scenario but AAI has managed to convince all of them, Malhotra said. 

There were phone calls from several countries and the AAF regarding the security issue. But we have convinced them that it will be taken care of and there is nothing to worry, he said. 

There will be elaborate security arrangements for the players. They will get enough security during their stay at the hotels and while moving around, he added. (PTI) 




